 "Leave her alone."

If you truly care about her

Appealing to that monster's most repulsive feeling made his blood boil.

This morning I attended classes, then had lunch, and spent the afternoon in the library working on my assignments.

 "Rita, it's time to go."

I woke up Rita, who had fallen asleep in a corner of the library as the sun began to set, and we left together.

Since escaping from the clutches of that demon, Rita became her bodyguard and personal escort, protecting her 24 hours a day. There was only one person Giselle needed to be protected from now.


Chapter 129.
Naturally, Rita ended up living at the Magnolia Terrace and even started accompanying her to her club activities.

 "And who is she?"

Barely had they crossed the threshold of the Patriotic Student Society club when a third-year cock coming down the stairs pointed at Giselle with his chin.

 "Miss Bishop's bodyguard."

The student rolled his eyes upon hearing Rita's answer. Few students at the academy needed an escort. Even those with chauffeurs or personal butlers rarely brought them into the classrooms. Giselle knew they murmured things like 'Does she think she's a princess just for being a Roselle?' but there was no other option.

 "Bodyguard? Is that really necessary? Miss Bishop, our club does not admit just anyone."

He pretended to worry about safety, but his tone when saying 'just anyone' and the dismissive glance toward Rita betrayed his displeasure.

