She had been watching that hand throughout the dinner. And Edwin, knowing this, had made sure to use it constantly, to show that no lasting mark remained, that he was fine, and that there was no need to keep feeling guilty.

 "Because of that madness of mine you ended up hurt."

But the truth was the reverse.

Giselle, it was I who, by acting recklessly, put you in danger.

Holding her hand, Edwin gently ran his thumb over the delicate knuckles that protruded on the back of her small hand.

If only I could also caress the wounds on your soul like this

She had carried so much damage from such a young age, and he, who only wanted to protect her, had done nothing but add new scars to that already marked heart.

