Giselle nodded, implying she shared that feeling. But the slight smile she drew seemed more like a reflex than a sincere expression. Even if her body was intact, was it as if she had lost a child in her soul?

Edwin noticed her hand beginning to loosen, and he held it more firmly, not letting go.

