She nodded immediately, without hesitation.

 "A child that will come later. When you are fully an adult. When your body and heart are ready"

Then, let's have one.

Why did she expect those words to complete the sentence?

 "I hope you can have a child someday with a man who is sound in both body and spirit, and whom you marry for love."

But what Edwin had just told her was nothing more than a veiled rejection.

Just as that demon had said: after everything that had happened, Edwin felt nothing for her.

How ashamed she felt now for daring to hope for something as crazy as a proposal. She wanted to disappear out of shame.

And yet, Edwin did not let go of her hand.

Thus continued his cruel tenderness.

 "Giselle, I am not rejecting your feelings."

His words demonstrated that he understood her emotions completely.

Hearing from his own mouth that he knew about her unrequited love, she felt she would die of sheer humiliation.

