Would he have gone after you, if I hadn't been in the way?

Giselle could not lie. No, he wouldn't have.

 "Since we are talking about this everything you suffered, it is my duty to bear it. And although it is a situation that defies all logic, if we consider it from common sense, marrying would be the most logical thing."

The proposal she herself had dreamed of until a few moments ago, now that he mentioned it, made her chest ache.

