He said it so naturally that it was disconcerting, but his words were anything but light.

Duke Eccleston giving up his lineage, his bloodline, and choosing to live alone for the rest of his life?

Even to Giselle, an outsider, that sounded like handing the dukedom over to others.

The reputation of the Ecclestons, built over centuries on the continent, was at stake.

Old guards like Duchess Roxworth would not stand idly by watching everything collapse.

And among the collateral branches, there would surely be those who raised their voices to impose their son as heir, unleashing chaos.

The mere rumor would shake the entire nobility.

And yet, Edwin, who more than anyone should foresee all this, had made his decision with full awareness.

