Either way, my intention was always to live single. I am just returning to the starting point.

How selfish I am.

Giselle knew he was thinking of himself and yet, she couldn't help but feel a petty relief knowing there would be no other woman in his life.

But what good was it that Edwin closed his heart to everyone if that also left her out?

'Even if I grow up and become a much more attractive woman, I won't have any chance of winning his heart'

The door was also closing for Giselle.

And if that was the end, the most dignified thing was to accept it gracefully and take a step back.

That was her last chance to save some of her pride

'With elegance with calm.'

She took a deep breath, silently.

And as she exhaled, with a gentle smile, she said:

