It was an unusual comment for him: Edwin didn't usually yield, but neither did he err on the side of arrogance. Giselle's eyes rounded in astonishment. The man, who until then had looked at her with that haughty gaze resting his chin on his hand, suddenly let out an awkward laugh, as if he could no longer bear the tension. His cheeks instantly flushed red.

