'As if humans weren't already beasts,' he seemed to think. He had instantly grasped Giselle's purpose: to teach them how to differentiate between the two.

 "I see the recruits are incompetent."

He mocked the two with disdain, but in his attitude toward Giselle, reverence and caution were mixed.

