Key weapons are never revealed to the enemy.

There was another difference, actually. Unlike Edwin's serene gaze, this lunatic was excessive. His eyes wandered aimlessly, like those of someone insecure.

She had explained it to the others beforehand: that detail also served to identify him. But, for some reason, today his eyes barely moved. Another useless method.

