That day was today: the decoration ceremony at the palace. If his other personality emerged while he was close to Edwin, she was to inform Mr. Royce; if he was far away, as he was now, she would harden her expression and give a signal. That's why her smile was harmlessa tacit message for Royce, who was watching from the entrance.

The eye contact lasted an instant. Edwin, following protocol, looked away towards the hall wall as soon as he confirmed that Dawson was next to Giselle.

In the grand hall, guarded by soldiers and escorts, with photographers and journalists mixed in, any scandal provoked by his "cursed personality" would be disastrous. Both for Edwin and for the demon within him.

 'If they lock the Duke in an asylum, I'll be condemned to seeing lunatics for the rest of my life. None would be as pretty as you.'

That entity feared confinement, as in prison camps. Giselle had discovered that weakness by unlocking its dialogues under hypnosis.

The monster wouldn't dare to ruin his image today; after all, tomorrow he didn't want to appear in scandalous headlines before being dragged into a cell or a sanatorium.

'Ha Pathetic.'

