It wasn't an aide, but Crown Princess Helena.

Why would she do such mundane work?

She was known for her arroganceshe despised even her own father for not being of royal blood. That she would stoop to servant's tasks was absurd. Edwin disguised his suspicion under a brief bow, but the princess looked at him with mocking eyes before he turned his gaze to the Queen.

The sovereign of Mercia was so small that, even one step up, Edwin could distinguish her graying crown. He lowered his neck to facilitate her hanging the medal.

 "Major, I value your services highly" she began, squeezing his hand tightly (as she did with everyone, despite her apparent fragility)  "But the last year lacked merit."

She alluded to his capture as a prisoner. She knew that the achievements of his subordinates under his system were also his own, but

