It was pressure for him to remain in the army.

A debt?

Even the demon in his mind laughed. Edwin also found it ridiculous.

The Queen spoke of "honor" in granting him the medal and the title of Knight, but for himalready overloaded with decorationsit only meant a few more letters in his name.

And there was no reason to yield. Absolute monarchy had been extinct for centuries. Kings were merely decorative symbols, although the House Crowley still used its wealth to manipulate nobles.

But against the Ecclestons they could do nothing.

 "Duke"

Even the astute Queen, with her agile mind and ability to quickly assess situations, must already understand the reality.

