With a skillful display of humility, she broke down the pride of the arrogant monarch to show herself as a fragile, lonely woman, appealing to Edwin's compassion and loyalty. Undoubtedly, it was more effective than direct pressure. That's why Edwin usually described her as "a cunning old fox."

