It was one of the three intelligence battalions. The First Battalion, in charge of internal counter-espionage and personnel protection, was nicknamed the "Sentinels." The Second Battalion, specializing in infiltration and intelligence gathering abroad, was called the "Ghosts."

And then there was the Third Battalion, more hidden than the ghosts, named the "Falcon's Talons" (Talon) for its way of swooping down on its targets with lethal speed. Its specialty: assassination.

"Knowledge only gains strength when put into action," read its official motto. But among its members, another, more direct one circulated:

